_why wrote about this phenomenon in CLOSURE:<p><a href="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/5764687/CLOSURE.pdf" rel="nofollow">https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/5764687/CLOSURE.pdf</a><p>The segment in question runs from about page 29 through 34.<p><pre><code>    I unfolded my napkin and got the silverware out. &quot;I don&#x27;t remember.&quot;
    She got out her phone.
    &quot;No, don&#x27;t go there.&quot;
    &quot;I. M. D. B.&quot; Her fingers.
    &quot;Oh, Cristian Douglas,&quot; I said. &quot;It was Cristian Douglas.&quot;
    Still typing, head leaned back, under the spell of her phone.</code></pre>

You may or may not be surprised to know that PHP supports it natively.<p><pre><code>    php5 -r &#x27;echo idate(&quot;B&quot;);&#x27;
</code></pre>
<a href="http://php.net/manual/en/function.idate.php" rel="nofollow">http://php.net/manual/en/function.idate.php</a>
